   <title>Monitoring Service Overview</title>
    
      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Installation</bridgehead>
      <para>The monitoring service is automatically installed as part of the <phrase/>
        installation.</para>

      <para>No specific configuration is required to use Monasca. However, you can configure the
        database for storing metrics as detailed in the <xref linkend="configure_monitoring"/> document.</para>

   
    
      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Differences Between Upstream and <phrase/>
        Implementations</bridgehead>
      <para>In the <phrase/> release, the OpenStack monitoring service,
        Monasca, is included as the monitoring solution with the following exceptions which are not
        included:</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Transform Engine</para>

         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Events Engine </para>

         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Anomaly and Prediction Engine</para>

         </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
      <note>
         <para>Icinga was supported in previous <phrase/> versions but it has been
        deprecated in <phrase/>.</para>

      </note>
   
    
